01:09.029 --> 01:11.432
Anyone not finished their Christmas shopping yet, be honest.

01:12.293 --> 01:13.936
Not even Amazon can save you tonight.

01:15.779 --> 01:23.570
I love the Christmas feeling, putting the slippers on, being around the family, tub of celebration, cinnamon candles burning,

01:24.066 --> 01:27.871
presence under the tree, and of course, the dad jokes.

01:29.994 --> 01:31.235
Dad, can I help you with one?

01:33.579 --> 01:34.460
All right, listen carefully.

01:34.480 --> 01:35.641
You've got to listen to this one.

01:36.202 --> 01:39.887
But a guy brought his wife a beautiful diamond ring for Christmas.

01:40.848 --> 01:49.019
After hearing about this extravagant gift, a friend of his said, I thought she wanted one of those new sporty four-wheel drive cars.

01:50.040 --> 01:51.442
She did, he replied,

01:52.098 --> 01:54.060
But where was I going to find a fake jeep?

01:57.504 --> 02:00.406
Yes, the TC boys enjoyed that.

02:00.587 --> 02:01.428
I enjoyed it too.

02:03.049 --> 02:06.252
Often, my wife says to me, she goes, I didn't get that joke.

02:06.272 --> 02:07.534
I said, well, I'll talk to you later.

02:08.234 --> 02:12.159
Often we talk about Christmas in terms of a feeling.

02:12.999 --> 02:15.081
But you know, Christmas isn't just a feeling.

02:15.502 --> 02:16.323
It's more than that.

02:16.903 --> 02:19.506
Christmas is actually a decision.

02:20.258 --> 02:22.741
We're going to dive dive into the nativity story.

02:23.502 --> 02:28.349
And we're going to look at a barely unknown character in the story.

02:28.409 --> 02:32.074
Often when we think about Christmas, we think of Mary and Joseph.

02:33.115 --> 02:35.017
We think of the wise men, the shepherds.

02:35.538 --> 02:38.842
But there's someone in the story that I've never spoken about much.

02:39.003 --> 02:40.044
I've never referenced him.

02:40.785 --> 02:47.634
And I want to draw attention to a relatively insignificant, yet significant character in the story.

02:48.834 --> 03:05.979
Just to familiarizes again with the Christmas story, the Virgin Mary and Joseph are traveling to Bethlehem because Roma, the Roman emperors Caesar Augustus has ordered a census requiring everyone to return to their ancestral hometown to register for taxation.

03:06.239 --> 03:08.503
Don't you just love talking about taxes even in church?

03:09.224 --> 03:14.371
Joseph had to go to Bethlehem and marry his pregnant wife travels with him.

03:14.992 --> 03:16.434
And in Luke chapter two,

03:16.738 --> 03:21.764
It says the time came for her child to be born and she gave birth to her firstborn son.

03:22.224 --> 03:30.394
She wrapped him in swaddling clothes and laid him in a manger because there was no room for him at the inn.

03:30.694 --> 03:33.177
I want to just focus on that one line this afternoon.

03:33.498 --> 03:41.387
Just for the next couple of hours, we're just going to focus on that one line.

03:41.607 --> 03:44.050
There was no room for him at the inn.

03:44.578 --> 04:00.840
The arrival of the greatest miracle in human history was standing at the door at that inn or that hospital that evening, the Messiah, the one that had been prophesied about 700 years ago, God and skin was about to arrive.

04:00.860 --> 04:10.674
And Mary and Joseph expected, like you should, to have their baby in a safe place, in a warm place, and they knocked on the door

04:10.818 --> 04:19.508
And somebody said, and we're assuming it, there was an innkeeper who says, I'm sorry, but there is no room for you at the inn.

04:20.649 --> 04:23.733
Completely oblivious to what's happening.

04:24.534 --> 04:29.940
I think, who knows that that's one of the most damning responses you could ever have as a pregnant mum, there is no room.

04:30.881 --> 04:38.450
I mean, we had our first child, and you go to the North Genorich Hospital, you get to the doors, and they say, not tonight, there's no room.

04:38.818 --> 04:42.543
but we do have a little shed out the back and just make it your own.

04:42.824 --> 04:43.845
Who knows, that's not right.

04:44.746 --> 04:48.591
Well, this is exactly what Mary and Joseph experienced.

04:50.314 --> 04:51.996
Think of the innkeeper knew that night.

04:52.036 --> 04:52.937
What was at stake?

04:52.978 --> 04:55.000
Things could be very different.

04:55.020 --> 05:00.147
If he only knew that letting Jesus in could have transformed his life and his future.

05:01.109 --> 05:04.914
If he had let Jesus in that night, he would have been a key part of the story too.

05:05.666 --> 05:16.657
Sometimes we can look at the innkeeper and I have over the years and think how could anyone not create a space for a pregnant mom to have a child, let alone to have the Savior of the world?

05:17.277 --> 05:19.279
Yet in some ways we can all do the same.

05:20.180 --> 05:30.870
Often in the hustle, the bustle, the busyness, the presence, all the things that happen this time of year, we can easily be guilty of saying there's no room actually for Jesus in this time.

05:31.771 --> 05:34.834
Santa can become the main character, and by the way, I love Santa.

05:35.394 --> 05:38.837
But Santa can become the main character of the story instead of the Savior.

05:39.518 --> 05:43.542
What we get can become more important than what we give.

05:44.443 --> 05:46.204
Exmas can replace Christmas.

05:47.105 --> 05:48.987
We can move Christ out of Christmas.

05:49.007 --> 05:50.688
There's no room for Christ anymore.

05:51.029 --> 05:55.313
I was reading this morning that some of the major streets in the country, they've removed Christmas.

05:55.773 --> 06:02.640
They've said there's no room for the Jesus factory in Christmas anymore because it's become so commercial.

06:04.181 --> 06:05.202
But the message

06:05.346 --> 06:08.430
This afternoon is to make room for Jesus this Christmas.

06:09.952 --> 06:13.417
Maybe you're visiting back from the wonder and we really welcome you back.

06:13.457 --> 06:16.481
Maybe you're popping in for the annual Christmas tradition.

06:16.841 --> 06:19.785
Or maybe when you come to church, you feel Christmas.

06:21.247 --> 06:25.112
Or maybe you're searching for truth right now in a world which seems so broken.

06:26.294 --> 06:29.618
But it's amazing what happens when we make that decision

06:30.850 --> 06:32.252
to allow room for Jesus.

06:32.433 --> 06:38.342
I want to just share really quickly three things that happen when we make room for Jesus at Christmas and beyond.

06:38.382 --> 06:41.147
Number one is this, you enjoy life more.

06:42.589 --> 06:45.795
In Luke chapter two verse 10, the angel said to them, do not be afraid.

06:46.175 --> 06:50.362
I bring you good news that will cause great joy for all the people.

06:50.863 --> 06:55.250
Jesus brings life to your life.

06:55.394 --> 06:56.716
He brings joy to your life.

06:56.916 --> 07:00.341
You know, we've had some amazing overwhelming feedback about the wonder.

07:00.361 --> 07:01.322
It was brilliant, wasn't it?

07:01.943 --> 07:06.950
It was just, but one of the things which we hear more and more is why are you all so happy?

07:08.552 --> 07:13.419
One guy said to me, he said, do you give your volunteers a little bit of drink before the shows?

07:16.363 --> 07:17.384
Believe it or not, we don't.

07:20.168 --> 07:24.754
Why did 500 volunteers show up for 13 shows?

07:25.218 --> 07:28.242
They're not getting paid to serve the wonder.

07:29.083 --> 07:32.328
Why were their children part of the wonder and the team?

07:32.368 --> 07:34.912
They were actually crying at the end and said, we'd never want this to stop.

07:36.694 --> 07:40.620
Because it was far more than just Rudolph or Sebastian or the Golden Boys.

07:42.703 --> 07:44.205
It was the spirit of the wonder.

07:45.386 --> 07:46.808
Some of you have asked that question.

07:46.868 --> 07:50.834
I wonder why they're so happy on heart sees Lane at number 55.

07:51.586 --> 07:55.773
I wonder why I walk in there and I feel different to walking around other places.

07:56.674 --> 07:59.298
It's not good vibes at Soul Church.

07:59.318 --> 08:06.390
It's simply that when you create space for Jesus, he fills you with what other things can't give you.

08:06.710 --> 08:08.093
He fills you with joy.

08:08.133 --> 08:09.695
He fills you with happiness.

08:10.016 --> 08:12.219
He gives you what money can't buy.

08:12.460 --> 08:14.583
He gives you what alcohol can't give you.

08:14.843 --> 08:18.930
He gives you something you can't even put into words.

08:20.130 --> 08:24.677
The shepherds were ordinary people, working people, busy people, tired people.

08:25.458 --> 08:30.565
But when they encounter Jesus, says that they were overcome with joy.

08:31.767 --> 08:35.593
You know, often when we think about happiness or joy, it comes from perfect circumstances.

08:35.613 --> 08:42.243
If I just had more money or if I just had more time or if I just had a bigger car, I would be happier or more joyful.

08:42.263 --> 08:45.868
But actually, joy doesn't actually have to come from perfect circumstances.

08:46.269 --> 08:49.874
Joy comes from being in the presence of Jesus.

08:51.330 --> 08:55.776
And those shepherds would have had many problems, lost sheep, sick sheep, depressed sheep.

08:56.417 --> 08:58.439
You name it, those shepherds would have had problems.

08:59.400 --> 08:59.961
But you know what?

08:59.981 --> 09:05.028
When they made room for Jesus that night, the Bible says they were overwhelmed with joy.

09:05.068 --> 09:11.736
Our theme for 2025 has been choose joy and it's been a challenging theme because you have to choose joy.

09:12.417 --> 09:15.281
But choosing joy is very difficult if you don't have Jesus.

09:16.302 --> 09:19.506
You see, when you choose Jesus, He gives you this gift of joy.

09:19.714 --> 09:27.064
And he can actually give you the sense and feeling of happiness and joy even when the circumstances of life aren't good.

09:28.126 --> 09:36.057
There's one thing I hear over and over that said this time of year into January and I've said it myself and see if you can relate to it.

09:36.117 --> 09:45.150
But when Christmas is over and sadly the lights are switched off and the tree comes down, we look back and say this, I should have enjoyed it a little bit more.

09:45.250 --> 09:46.632
Has anyone ever said that at Christmas?

09:47.132 --> 09:48.274
I should have enjoyed it more.

09:48.674 --> 09:57.168
We see we get so busy trying to feel Christmas, we can actually lose the very joy and the very meaning of Christmas, the thing we desire the most.

09:57.989 --> 09:59.612
But joy, you see, is a decision.

10:00.173 --> 10:00.854
It's a decision.

10:01.275 --> 10:02.436
Christmas is a decision.

10:02.857 --> 10:05.461
And the decision is to make room for Jesus.

10:07.425 --> 10:09.748
