18:06.607 --> 18:08.790
Yeah, let's congratulate everyone who said that prayer.

18:16.361 --> 18:18.804
Pray that you sense Jesus, the presence of Jesus.

18:19.705 --> 18:23.150
We want to give you a gift after we're going to be concluding the service in just a few moments.

18:23.210 --> 18:26.034
And down here, this is my friend, Treco,

18:26.178 --> 18:29.803
There's a little chapel area there and if you'd like to say, hey, I lifted up my hand.

18:29.823 --> 18:30.764
We want to give you a Bible.

18:30.784 --> 18:32.946
It's really the next step or out in the forest.

18:32.967 --> 18:34.048
Our team will have Bibles.

18:34.589 --> 18:37.412
Hey, if you want to have a conversation about what is the next step from here?

18:37.732 --> 18:41.317
The next step to keep allowing space and room in your life of Jesus.

18:41.417 --> 18:44.621
We'd love to help you as you make that decision.

18:44.641 --> 18:46.503
I just want to pray for one more group of people.

18:48.025 --> 18:51.730
I want to pray for for those who say, hey,

18:53.250 --> 18:55.332
I just want to really receive peace at Christmas.

18:55.412 --> 19:08.687
I know God, but really struggling to set on my mind, to set on my thoughts and so many distractions, so many disappointments in 2025, but I just really want God's peace to come and fill me.

19:08.727 --> 19:17.817
Maybe, you know, I was speaking to someone today, this is John, I'm really not looking forward to Christmas because some of the family died, but Jesus can come into the middle of the mix.

19:18.458 --> 19:22.482
He can come into the middle of the mess that you're facing and he just wants to bring peace.

19:22.850 --> 19:25.594
I believe that God can turn around your situation.

19:26.195 --> 19:29.319
If you just say, what I want you to do at the end of my prayer is just to say amen.

19:29.359 --> 19:30.000
Is that okay?

19:30.401 --> 19:31.542
You don't have to lift your hand up.

19:31.602 --> 19:32.664
You don't have to do anything.

19:32.824 --> 19:40.214
I'm just gonna say a simple prayer that God will bring peace into your home, into your family, into your heart, into your mind this Christmas.

19:40.715 --> 19:46.303
And I believe that we can still have a happy Christmas despite all the unhappiness around us.

19:46.323 --> 19:46.984
Do you believe that?

19:47.905 --> 19:51.250
So Father God, we just pray right now for everyone who's unsettled,

19:51.554 --> 19:56.281
Everyone who's struggling, maybe with anxiety, those who've had a really difficult year.

19:56.882 --> 19:59.466
We just pray, Father, that you would fill them with your peace.

20:00.187 --> 20:02.530
You would just go ahead of them in every situation.

20:03.071 --> 20:06.837
Lord, we pray that there would be no conflict at home around the tables this year.

20:07.177 --> 20:11.203
It would just be a time where Emmanuel would be with us afresh.

20:11.764 --> 20:15.930
We thank you, Lord, for the promise that you never leave us and you never forsake us.

20:16.271 --> 20:21.298
So I speak peace over our church community, over every family here today.

20:21.666 --> 20:23.408
in your name, the name of Jesus.

20:23.768 --> 20:24.289
Amen.

20:25.210 --> 20:25.570
Amen.

20:31.797 --> 20:33.039
Thanks again for tuning in.

20:33.780 --> 20:46.354
If you said yes to Jesus today by saying the Salvation Prayer, we'd love for you to email connections at soulchurch.com so we can talk to you a little bit more about this incredible decision you've just made.

20:46.722 --> 20:55.218
And if at any point in the service, you felt moved to give towards any of our local or global initiatives, head to SoulChurch.com.

20:55.238 --> 21:02.070
And don't forget to stay connected with us on Facebook, Instagram, and YouTube by searching at SoulChurchUK.

21:02.651 --> 21:04.114
Take care and God bless.

